1 (2) “COUNTY BOARD” MEANS THE PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY
2 BOARD OF EDUCATION.
3 (3) “ELIGIBLE TAXPAYER” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO:
4 (I) 1. IS THE PARENT OF A SCHOOL STUDENT; OR
5 2. HAS LEGAL CUSTODY OF A SCHOOL STUDENT AS A
6 LEGAL GUARDIAN; AND
7 (II) VOLUNTEERS AT THE SCHOOL IN WHICH THE STUDENT IS
8 ENROLLED.
9 (4) “SCHOOL” MEANS A PUBLIC OR NONPUBLIC ELEMENTARY OR
10 SECONDARY SCHOOL IN PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY, INCLUDING A CHARTER
11 SCHOOL.
12 (B) SUBJECT TO THE LIMITATIONS OF THIS SECTION, EACH ELIGIBLE
13 TAXPAYER, REGARDLESS OF INDIVIDUAL OR JOINT FILING STATUS, MAY CLAIM A
14 CREDIT AGAINST THE STATE INCOME TAX IN THE AMOUNT STATED ON A TAX CREDIT
15 CERTIFICATE ISSUED TO THE ELIGIBLE TAXPAYER DURING THE TAXABLE YEAR IN
16 ACCORDANCE WITH SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION.
17 (C) (1) THE STATE DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION SHALL, IN
18 CONSULTATION WITH THE COMPTROLLER, DEVELOP AND MAKE AVAILABLE AN
19 APPLICATION AND A TAX CREDIT CERTIFICATE TO BE USED IN ACCORDANCE WITH
20 PARAGRAPHS (2) AND (3) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
21 (2) AN ELIGIBLE TAXPAYER SHALL SUBMIT AN APPLICATION FOR A
22 CREDIT UNDER THIS SECTION:
23 (I) IF THE STUDENT IS ENROLLED IN A PUBLIC SCHOOL, TO THE
24 COUNTY BOARD MEMBER WHO REPRESENTS THE SCHOOL; OR
25 (II) IF THE STUDENT IS ENROLLED IN A NONPUBLIC SCHOOL, TO
26 AN ADMINISTRATOR OF THE SCHOOL.
27 (3) (I) ON APPLICATION BY AN ELIGIBLE TAXPAYER UNDER
28 PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, A COUNTY BOARD MEMBER OR SCHOOL
29 ADMINISTRATOR SHALL ISSUE A TAX CREDIT CERTIFICATE IN AN AMOUNT EQUAL TO
30 $20 FOR EACH HOUR THAT THE ELIGIBLE TAXPAYER VOLUNTEERS AT THE SCHOOL
31 IN WHICH THE STUDENT IS ENROLLED.

